{"article_id":"ls6xVhKXGgup7wCB","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"The nation 's unemployment rate edged up to 7.9 percent in October from 7.8 percent in September ,","depth":5},{"id":1,"text":"the Bureau of Labor Statistics says .","depth":5},{"id":2,"text":"But private and public employers added 171,000 jobs to their payrolls","depth":5},{"id":3,"text":"- nearly 50,000 more","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"than economists had expected .","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"So the news is somewhat mixed :","depth":4},{"id":6,"text":"While the jobless rate remained stuck near 8 percent ,","depth":5},{"id":7,"text":"job growth was better than forecast .","depth":5},{"id":8,"text":"We 'll have more from the report and reactions to it","depth":6},{"id":9,"text":"as the morning continues .","depth":6},{"id":10,"text":"Hit your refresh button","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"to be sure","depth":9},{"id":12,"text":"you 're seeing our latest updates .","depth":9},{"id":13,"text":"Or , click these links for :","depth":7},{"id":14,"text":"-- Why the jobless rate went up","depth":7},{"id":15,"text":"even as more jobs were added to payrolls .","depth":7},{"id":16,"text":"Update at 11:35 a.m . ET .","depth":4},{"id":17,"text":"Romney Focuses On Obama 's Record :","depth":6},{"id":18,"text":"At 7.9 percent , the jobless rate is more than 2 points higher","depth":10},{"id":19,"text":"than President Obama said","depth":11},{"id":20,"text":"it would be by this time in his administration ,","depth":11},{"id":21,"text":"Republican presidential nominee Mitt Romney just told supporters in Wisconsin .","depth":9},{"id":22,"text":"The difference equals 9 million fewer jobs","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"than Obama had predicted ,","depth":10},{"id":24,"text":"according to Romney .","depth":9},{"id":25,"text":"He has also echoed comments","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"he made earlier","depth":9},{"id":27,"text":"about the economy not getting on track during Obama 's time in office .","depth":8},{"id":28,"text":"Update at 10:55 a.m . ET .","depth":5},{"id":29,"text":"Obama Hails Growth ,","depth":10},{"id":30,"text":"But Says","depth":11},{"id":31,"text":"`` We 've Got More Work To Do '' :","depth":11},{"id":32,"text":"At a campaign rally in Ohio , President Obama just pointed to some of the good news in the report ,","depth":12},{"id":33,"text":"including the word","depth":13},{"id":34,"text":"that private employers added `` more workers in October","depth":15},{"id":35,"text":"[ 184,000 ]","depth":15},{"id":36,"text":"than at any time in the last eight months . ''","depth":14},{"id":37,"text":"In February , private payrolls rose by 254,000 jobs .","depth":11},{"id":38,"text":"`` We 've made real progress ,","depth":12},{"id":39,"text":"but we are here today","depth":13},{"id":40,"text":"because we know","depth":14},{"id":41,"text":"we have more work to do , ''","depth":14},{"id":42,"text":"Obama added .","depth":11},{"id":43,"text":"Earlier , Republican presidential nominee Mitt Romney said","depth":10},{"id":44,"text":"that `` today 's increase in the unemployment rate is a sad reminder","depth":11},{"id":45,"text":"that the economy is at a virtual standstill . ''","depth":11},{"id":46,"text":"Update at 9:40 a.m . ET .","depth":9},{"id":47,"text":"Economy Is `` Continuing To Heal , ''","depth":10},{"id":48,"text":"White House Says :","depth":10},{"id":49,"text":"`` While more work remains to be done ,","depth":12},{"id":50,"text":"today 's employment report provides further evidence","depth":13},{"id":51,"text":"that the U.S. economy is continuing to heal from the wounds","depth":14},{"id":52,"text":"inflicted by the worst downturn since the Great Depression , ''","depth":14},{"id":53,"text":"Alan Krueger , chairman of the Council of Economic Advisers , says in a statement","depth":12},{"id":54,"text":"just released by the White House .","depth":12},{"id":55,"text":"`` Over the last 12 months , the economy has added a total of 2.1 million jobs ,","depth":11},{"id":56,"text":"as compared to 1.9 million over the preceding 12 months . ''","depth":11},{"id":57,"text":"Update at 9:30 a.m . ET .","depth":8},{"id":58,"text":"More On The Differences Between The Surveys :","depth":9},{"id":59,"text":"As we said earlier ,","depth":12},{"id":60,"text":"BLS really does two reports .","depth":12},{"id":61,"text":"One is based on a survey of employers","depth":13},{"id":62,"text":"( it concluded","depth":14},{"id":63,"text":"that 171,000 jobs were added to payrolls )","depth":14},{"id":64,"text":"and one is based on a survey of households","depth":13},{"id":65,"text":"( it concluded","depth":14},{"id":66,"text":"that the jobless rate rose to 7.9 percent ) .","depth":14},{"id":67,"text":"John Galvin , the acting commissioner at BLS , says in a statement","depth":13},{"id":68,"text":"that :","depth":13},{"id":69,"text":"`` The household survey and establishment survey employment measures often show different month-to-month changes .","depth":13},{"id":70,"text":"The establishment survey employment series has a smaller margin of error than the household survey","depth":16},{"id":71,"text":"because of its much larger sample size .","depth":16},{"id":72,"text":"An over-the-month employment change of about 100,000 is statistically significant in the establishment survey ,","depth":16},{"id":73,"text":"while the threshold for a statistically significant change in the household survey is about 400,000 .","depth":16},{"id":74,"text":"However , the household survey has a more expansive scope than the establishment survey","depth":15},{"id":75,"text":"because it includes the self-employed , agricultural workers , and other workers","depth":16},{"id":76,"text":"who are excluded by the establishment survey .","depth":16},{"id":77,"text":"Over longer periods of time , the employment measures from the two surveys tend to track more closely . ''","depth":11},{"id":78,"text":"Update at 9:15 a.m . ET .","depth":8},{"id":79,"text":"Romney Says","depth":11},{"id":80,"text":"Economy Is `` At A Virtual Standstill '' :","depth":11},{"id":81,"text":"`` Today 's increase in the unemployment rate is a sad reminder","depth":13},{"id":82,"text":"that the economy is at a virtual standstill , ''","depth":13},{"id":83,"text":"Republican presidential nominee Mitt Romney says in a statement","depth":13},{"id":84,"text":"just released by his campaign .","depth":13},{"id":85,"text":"`` The jobless rate is higher","depth":13},{"id":86,"text":"than it was","depth":14},{"id":87,"text":"when President Obama took office ,","depth":14},{"id":88,"text":"and there are still 23 million Americans","depth":13},{"id":89,"text":"struggling for work . ''","depth":13},{"id":90,"text":"In the year","depth":13},{"id":91,"text":"before President Obama took office ,","depth":13},{"id":92,"text":"the jobless rate rose from 5 percent in January 2008 to 7.8 percent in January 2009 .","depth":12},{"id":93,"text":"The rate then continued upward , to a recent peak of 10 percent in October 2009 .","depth":13},{"id":94,"text":"It did n't drop back below 8 percent until this September .","depth":13},{"id":95,"text":"Planet Money has charted the 22 million Americans","depth":13},{"id":96,"text":"who are `` unemployed","depth":14},{"id":97,"text":"or ca n't find full-time work . ''","depth":14},{"id":98,"text":"Update at 9:10 a.m . ET .","depth":10},{"id":99,"text":"Another Way","depth":11},{"id":100,"text":"Of Looking At","depth":12},{"id":101,"text":"Why The Jobless Rate Went Up :","depth":12},{"id":102,"text":"-- 578,000 people reported","depth":12},{"id":103,"text":"they had joined the labor force ,","depth":13},{"id":104,"text":"either by finding work","depth":14},{"id":105,"text":"or just by looking for a job . --","depth":14},{"id":106,"text":"So , the ranks of the unemployed grew by about 170,000 .","depth":11},{"id":107,"text":"Reminder :","depth":15},{"id":108,"text":"BLS is really reporting on two surveys :","depth":17},{"id":109,"text":"One of households and one of employers .","depth":17},{"id":110,"text":"Two surveys mean two sets of results","depth":17},{"id":111,"text":"that sometimes seem to say different things .","depth":17},{"id":112,"text":"In this case , though , both surveys are showing job growth in October .","depth":14},{"id":113,"text":"Update at 9 a.m . ET .","depth":13},{"id":114,"text":"Households Report Even Stronger Job Growth :","depth":14},{"id":115,"text":"Though public and private employers said","depth":16},{"id":116,"text":"they added 171,000 jobs to their payrolls ,","depth":16},{"id":117,"text":"the BLS says","depth":17},{"id":118,"text":"its survey of households indicates","depth":18},{"id":119,"text":"that 410,000 more Americans report","depth":19},{"id":120,"text":"they were working in October .","depth":19},{"id":121,"text":"That follows an increase of 873,000 in that figure from August to September .","depth":16},{"id":122,"text":"As we explained last month ,","depth":14},{"id":123,"text":"the agency 's two surveys","depth":16},{"id":124,"text":"- one of employers and the other of households -","depth":16},{"id":125,"text":"can produce different results .","depth":15},{"id":126,"text":"`` Four years of persistently high unemployment and long-term joblessness might be the best","depth":15},{"id":127,"text":"President Obama can do","depth":15},{"id":128,"text":"-","depth":14},{"id":129,"text":"but it 's nowhere near what the American people can do","depth":14},{"id":130,"text":"if we get Washington out of their way , ''","depth":14},{"id":131,"text":"House Speaker John Boehner","depth":14},{"id":132,"text":"( R-Ohio )","depth":14},{"id":133,"text":"says in a statement","depth":14},{"id":134,"text":"just released by his office .","depth":14},{"id":135,"text":"Update at 8:45 a.m . ET .","depth":10},{"id":136,"text":"Why Did The Jobless Rate Go Up ?","depth":7},{"id":137,"text":"When job growth is stronger than forecast","depth":11},{"id":138,"text":"but the unemployment rate still rises ,","depth":11},{"id":139,"text":"economists look at whether more people joined the labor force","depth":10},{"id":140,"text":"- hopefully because many of them are optimistic","depth":10},{"id":141,"text":"about being able to find work .","depth":10},{"id":142,"text":"According to BLS ,","depth":11},{"id":143,"text":"`` the civilian labor force rose by 578,000 to 155.6 million in October ,","depth":12},{"id":144,"text":"and the labor force participation rate edged up to 63.8 percent","depth":13},{"id":145,"text":"[ from 63.6 percent ] . ''","depth":13},{"id":146,"text":"Meanwhile , `` there were 813,000 discouraged workers in October , a decline of 154,000 from a year earlier .","depth":11},{"id":147,"text":"'' Discouraged workers are those folks","depth":13},{"id":148,"text":"who are n't looking for work ``","depth":13},{"id":149,"text":"because they believe","depth":13},{"id":150,"text":"no jobs are available for them . ''","depth":13},{"id":151,"text":"Those figures may signal","depth":11},{"id":152,"text":"that the jobless rate stayed near 8 percent","depth":12},{"id":153,"text":"in part because of good news","depth":13},{"id":154,"text":"-","depth":14},{"id":155,"text":"that more Americans are feeling better about the economy","depth":15},{"id":156,"text":"and have decided to start looking for work .","depth":15},{"id":157,"text":"That increased the size of the labor force , though ,","depth":11},{"id":158,"text":"and helped lift the jobless rate a tenth of a point .","depth":11},{"id":159,"text":"Update at 8:40 a.m . ET .","depth":9},{"id":160,"text":"September Job Growth Revised Up :","depth":10},{"id":161,"text":"There were 148,000 jobs added to payrolls in September ,","depth":12},{"id":162,"text":"BLS now says .","depth":12},{"id":163,"text":"That 's up from the agency 's initial estimate of 114,000 .","depth":11},{"id":164,"text":"Our original post","depth":9},{"id":165,"text":"( from 7 a.m . ET ) .","depth":9},{"id":166,"text":"`` Jobless Rate Likely Edged Up In October ,","depth":10},{"id":167,"text":"Job Growth Was Likely Modest '' :","depth":10},{"id":168,"text":"The last major economic report before Election Day is due at 8:30 a.m . ET","depth":10},{"id":169,"text":"and economists say","depth":12},{"id":170,"text":"we should expect to hear","depth":12},{"id":171,"text":"that the unemployment rate ticked up to 7.9 percent in October from September 's estimated 7.8 percent","depth":12},{"id":172,"text":"and that payrolls grew by just 125,000 jobs .","depth":12},{"id":173,"text":"Whatever the Bureau of Labor Statistics says ,","depth":10},{"id":174,"text":"the news is sure to be a hot topic on the campaign trail and among political pundits .","depth":10},{"id":175,"text":"As you 've surely heard many times :","depth":11},{"id":176,"text":"-- Republican presidential nominee Mitt Romney says","depth":13},{"id":177,"text":"President Obama 's economic policies have n't done enough","depth":14},{"id":178,"text":"to spur job growth","depth":15},{"id":179,"text":"and bring down unemployment .","depth":15},{"id":180,"text":"-- The president has been touting the slow job growth and gradual decline in unemployment since the jobless rate 's recent peak of 10 percent in October 2009 .","depth":13},{"id":181,"text":"He says","depth":14},{"id":182,"text":"they 're signs","depth":15},{"id":183,"text":"the economy is on the right track .","depth":15},{"id":184,"text":"Meanwhile , some skeptics","depth":12},{"id":185,"text":"- such as former General Electric CEO Jack Welch -","depth":12},{"id":186,"text":"will be watching closely","depth":12},{"id":187,"text":"to see","depth":13},{"id":188,"text":"if the BLS report fits with their view of how the economy is doing .","depth":13},{"id":189,"text":"We 'll update this post with the news","depth":4},{"id":190,"text":"after the report is released ,","depth":4},{"id":191,"text":"and follow with highlights and reactions .","depth":3},{"id":192,"text":"Also check Planet Money for economic analysis and It 's All Politics for more on how the report might affect the campaign .","depth":2}],"relations":[{"parent":385,"left":381,"right":384,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":381,"left":200,"right":380,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":200,"left":197,"right":199,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":197,"left":194,"right":196,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":194,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":196,"left":2,"right":195,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":195,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":199,"left":5,"right":198,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":198,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":380,"left":208,"right":379,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":208,"left":207,"right":16,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":207,"left":201,"right":206,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":201,"left":8,"right":9,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":206,"left":204,"right":205,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":204,"left":203,"right":13,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":203,"left":10,"right":202,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":202,"left":11,"right":12,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":205,"left":14,"right":15,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":379,"left":219,"right":378,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":219,"left":218,"right":28,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":218,"left":17,"right":217,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":217,"left":214,"right":216,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":214,"left":211,"right":213,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":211,"left":210,"right":21,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":210,"left":18,